 <span data-ttu-id="103b0-103"><xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> influisce solo su un <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> quando è attiva (dopo il <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> inizia).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="103b0-103"><xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> only affects a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> when it is active (after the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> starts).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="103b0-104">Per controllare un <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>, il <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> deve fare riferimento al <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Name%2A> del <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard> che controlla che <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="103b0-104">To control a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>, the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> must reference the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Name%2A> of the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard> that controls that <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="103b0-105">Visualizzare [procedura: usare i trigger di evento per controllare un Storyboard dopo il relativo avvio](~/docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/how-to-use-event-triggers-to-control-a-storyboard-after-it-starts.md) per un esempio.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="103b0-105">See [How to: Use Event Triggers to Control a Storyboard After It Starts](~/docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/how-to-use-event-triggers-to-control-a-storyboard-after-it-starts.md) for an example.</span></span>  
  
